

Entry
Purpose: Represents one journal entry.
Responsibilities:

Store the date, prompt, and user’s response

Display itself

Convert itself to a savable string

Reconstruct itself from a saved string


-------------------------------
|           Entry             |
-------------------------------
| - _date : string            |
| - _prompt : string          |
| - _response : string        |
-------------------------------
| + Entry(date, prompt, resp) |
| + Display()                 |
| + ToFileFormat() : string   |
| + FromFileFormat(line):Entry|
-------------------------------



Journal
Purpose: Holds all entries and manages them.
Responsibilities:

Store a list of Entry objects

Add new entries

Display all entries

Save entries to a file

Load entries from a file


------------------------------------
|             Journal              |
------------------------------------
| - _entries : List<Entry>         |
------------------------------------
| + AddEntry(entry)                |
| + DisplayAll()                   |
| + SaveToFile(filename)           |
| + LoadFromFile(filename)         |
------------------------------------



PromptGenerator
Purpose: Provide random writing prompts.
Responsibilities:

Store a list of prompts

Return a random prompt when asked


------------------------------------
|        PromptGenerator           |
------------------------------------
| - _prompts : List<string>        |
| - _rng : Random                  |
------------------------------------
| + GetRandomPrompt() : string     |
------------------------------------

